13/06/2003
UGLJEVIK, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Russian personnel assigned to SFOR handed over a military facility to local authorities in Ugljevik on Friday (13 June), wrapping up seven years of participation in the peacekeeping mission. Commanders said the unit had improved the road infrastructure, planted trees and built the Aleksandr Nevskiy Cathedral as well as three monuments dedicated to Serbian-Russian friendship and military co-operation during World War II. (ITAR-TASS, BBC - 13/06/03)
